 The headers of the 'readthedocs' theme have their colors overriden by css inside in the html pages making it unable to override the default css using a custom CSS file.

```
  <style>
    body {font-size: 90%;}
    pre, code {font-size: 100%;}
    h3, h4, h5, h6 {color: #2980b9; font-weight: 300}
  </style> 
```

If you have a nav with a bunch of items and then make the screen height too small so that a scrollbar appears, the scrollbar won't go all the way down, because the prev, next, Github footer thing is covering it.

You can fix this by adding a CSS rule like:

``` css
.wy-menu-vertical ul {
    margin-bottom: 2em;
}
```

though you may prefer another approach. This works though.

